{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:proverbs.2",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "proverbs",
    "chapterNumber": 2,
    "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2",
    "summary": "Source text for Proverbs 2 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:1",
      "text": "My son, if you receive my words and treasure up my commandments with you,",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:2",
      "text": "making your ear attentive to wisdom and inclining your heart to understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:3",
      "text": "yes, if you cry out for insight and raise your voice for understanding,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:4",
      "text": "if you seek it like silver and search for it as for hidden treasures;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:5",
      "text": "then you will understand the fear of the Lord and find the knowledge of God.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:6",
      "text": "For the Lord gives wisdom; from his mouth come knowledge and understanding;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:7",
      "text": "he stores up sound wisdom for the upright; he is a shield to those who walk in integrity,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:8",
      "text": "guarding the paths of justice and preserving the way of his saints.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:9",
      "text": "Then you will understand righteousness and justice and equity, every good path;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:10",
      "text": "for wisdom will come into your heart, and knowledge will be pleasant to your soul;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:11",
      "text": "discretion will watch over you; understanding will guard you;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:12",
      "text": "delivering you from the way of evil, from men of perverted speech,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:13",
      "text": "who forsake the paths of uprightness to walk in the ways of darkness,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:14",
      "text": "who rejoice in doing evil and delight in the perverseness of evil;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:15",
      "text": "men whose paths are crooked, and who are devious in their ways.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:16",
      "text": "You will be saved from the loose woman, from the adventuress with her smooth words,",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:17",
      "text": "who forsakes the companion of her youth and forgets the covenant of her God;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:18",
      "text": "for her house sinks down to death, and her paths to the shades;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:19",
      "text": "none who go to her come back nor do they regain the paths of life.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:20",
      "text": "So you will walk in the way of good men and keep to the paths of the righteous.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.21",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 21,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:21",
      "text": "For the upright will inhabit the land, and men of integrity will remain in it;",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:proverbs.2.22",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "proverbs",
      "chapterNumber": 2,
      "verseNumber": 22,
      "referenceLabel": "Proverbs 2:22",
      "text": "but the wicked will be cut off from the land, and the treacherous will be rooted out of it.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
